1858  // should be 1.0, since it's active.
1859  Dbg_Assert( blendVal[0] == 1.0f );
1860 
1861  float totalBlendVal = 0.0f;
1862  for ( int i = 1; i < numBlendChannels; i++ )
1863  {
1864  if ( blendVal[i] )
1865  {
1866  totalBlendVal += 1.0f;
1867  }
1868  }
1869

1871  for ( int i = 1; i < numBlendChannels; i++ )
1872  {
1873  degenerateBlendTotal += blendVal[i];
1874  }
1875 
1876  // normalize them so that they all add up to total blend value
1877  blendVal[0] = totalBlendVal - degenerateBlendTotal;
1878 
1879  // Scan through the sets of frames, interpolating between the 2 based on the blend values.
1880  float sum = 0.0f;
1881 
1882  int i0, i1;
1883  for ( i1 = (numBlendChannels - 1); i1 > 0; --i1 )
1884  {
1885  float blend1 = blendVal[i1];
1886  if ( blend1 )
1887  {
1888  blend1 += sum;
1889 
1890  i0 = i1 - 1;
1891  while(( blendVal[i0] <= 0.0f ) && ( i0 > 0 ))
1892  {
1893  --i0;
1894  }
1895 
1896  float blend0 = blendVal[i0];
1897 
1898  sum += blendVal[i1];
1899 
1900  // Need to normalise blend0 and blend1 so they sum to 1.0.
1901  blend0 /= ( blend0 + blend1 );
1902  blend1 = 1.0f - blend0;
1903 
1904  Mth::Quat* pRotations0 = pPoseList[i0].m_rotations;
1905  Mth::Quat* pRotations1 = pPoseList[i1].m_rotations;
1906  Mth::Vector* pTranslations0 = pPoseList[i0].m_translations;
1907  Mth::Vector* pTranslations1 = pPoseList[i1].m_translations;
1908

1910  {
1911  *pRotations0 = Mth::FastSlerp( *pRotations0, *pRotations1, 1.0f - blend0 );
1912 
1913  *pTranslations0 = Mth::Lerp( *pTranslations0, *pTranslations1, 1.0f - blend0 );
1914 
1915  pRotations0++;
1916  pRotations1++;
1917  pTranslations0++;
1918  pTranslations1++;
1919  }
1920  }
1921  }

1924

1930
